==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
*A primary verb

===Pronunciation===
*βάπτω / baptō / bap'-to

===Verb===
'''βάπτω'''

# in the New Testament only in a qualified or specific sense, that is, to [[whelm]], that is, cover wholly with a fluid;  (literally) to [[moisten]] (a part of one’s person), or (by implication) to [[stain]] (as with dye): - [[dip]].

